The House Committee on Intragovernmental Coordination - Local Legislation offers the
following substitute to HB 615:
A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend an Act creating the Chatham County Recreation Authority, approved April 5, 1995
2 (Ga. L. 1995, p. 4281), so as to revise the membership of the authority; to provide for new
3 board membership; to provide terms of office; to revise quorum requirements; to provide for
4 related matters; to provide an effective date; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other
5 purposes.
6 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
7 SECTION 1.
8 An Act creating the Chatham County Recreation Authority, approved April 5, 1995
9 (Ga. L. 1995, p. 4281), is amended in Section 2 by revising subsections (b) and (h) as
10 follows:
11 "(b)(1) On July 1, 2025, and until February 28, 2029, the authority shall be governed by
12 a board that shall consist of no more than 14 members. As of March 1, 2029, the
13 authority shall be governed by a board that shall consist of nine members.
14 (2)(A) Those members of the authority serving on the effective date of this subsection
15 shall serve out the terms to which they were appointed; provided, however, that any
16 vacancy on the board:
